<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>On the Cut — Support</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --navy: #0a1f44;
            --navy-light: #14306a;
            --blue: #4a90e2;
            --sky: #7fb2f0;
            --bg: #f7f9fc;
            --card: #ffffff;
            --text: #1a1a1a;
            --muted: #5e6b7e;
            --border: #e3e9f2;
        }
        * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
        body {
            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.65;
            color: var(--text);
            background: var(--bg);
        }

        /* Header */
        header {
            background: linear-gradient(160deg, var(--navy) 0%, var(--navy-light) 100%);
            color: #fff;
            padding: 56px 24px 48px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .logo {
            width: 88px;
            height: 88px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            margin-bottom: 18px;
            border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.15);
        }
        .logo svg { width: 52px; height: 52px; }
        header h1 { font-size: 30px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.5px; }
        header .tagline { font-size: 16px; opacity: 0.75; margin-top: 4px; }
        header .pill {
            display: inline-block;
            margin-top: 18px;
            padding: 7px 16px;
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
            border-radius: 100px;
            font-size: 13px;
            letter-spacing: 0.3px;
        }

        /* Layout */
        .container { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }
        .section { margin: 44px auto; }
        .section h2 {
            font-size: 13px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 1.2px;
            color: var(--blue);
            margin-bottom: 18px;
            font-weight: 700;
        }

        /* Cards */
        .card {
            background: var(--card);
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 16px;
            padding: 4px 24px;
            box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(10,31,68,0.04);
        }
        details {
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
            padding: 18px 0;
        }
        details:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
        summary {
            font-weight: 600;
            font-size: 16px;
            cursor: pointer;
            list-style: none;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            color: var(--navy);
        }
        summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
        summary::after {
            content: "+";
            font-size: 22px;
            color: var(--blue);
            font-weight: 400;
            margin-left: 16px;
        }
        details[open] summary::after { content: "–"; }
        details p {
            margin-top: 12px;
            color: var(--muted);
            font-size: 15px;
        }

        /* Feature grid */
        .grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 16px; }
        @media (max-width: 560px) { .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
        .feature {
            background: var(--card);
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 14px;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .feature .icon {
            width: 40px; height: 40px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            background: rgba(74,144,226,0.12);
            display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
        }
        .feature .icon svg { width: 22px; height: 22px; stroke: var(--blue); }
        .feature h3 { font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 4px; color: var(--navy); }
        .feature p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--muted); }

        /* Contact */
        .contact {
            background: linear-gradient(160deg, var(--navy) 0%, var(--navy-light) 100%);
            color: #fff;
            border-radius: 18px;
            padding: 36px 28px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .contact h2 { color: var(--sky); }
        .contact p { opacity: 0.85; margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 15px; }
        .contact a.btn {
            display: inline-block;
            background: #fff;
            color: var(--navy);
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 600;
            padding: 13px 28px;
            border-radius: 100px;
            font-size: 15px;
        }
        .contact .small { font-size: 13px; opacity: 0.6; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 0; }

        /* Safety banner */
        .safety {
            background: #fff7ed;
            border: 1px solid #fed7aa;
            border-radius: 14px;
            padding: 18px 20px;
            display: flex;
            gap: 14px;
            align-items: flex-start;
        }
        .safety svg { width: 22px; height: 22px; stroke: #ea580c; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px; }
        .safety p { font-size: 14px; color: #7c2d12; }

        footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 40px 24px 60px;
            color: var(--muted);
            font-size: 13px;
            line-height: 1.7;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <div class="logo">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M3 14h18l-2 5H5l-2-5z"/>
                <path d="M5 14V9h9l3 5"/>
                <circle cx="8" cy="11" r="1"/>
            </svg>
        </div>
        <h1>On the Cut</h1>
        <div class="tagline">Canal navigation &amp; planning</div>
        <div class="pill">Help &amp; Support</div>
    </header>

    <div class="container">

        <!-- Getting started -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>Getting Started</h2>
            <div class="grid">
                <div class="feature">
                    <div class="icon">
                        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="10" r="3"/><path d="M12 2a8 8 0 0 0-8 8c0 5.4 8 12 8 12s8-6.6 8-12a8 8 0 0 0-8-8z"/></svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Plan a route</h3>
                    <p>Tap Set Start, then Set End. The app snaps to the nearest canal and plans the way between them.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature">
                    <div class="icon">
                        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M3 11l19-9-9 19-2-8-8-2z"/></svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Navigate</h3>
                    <p>Once a route is planned, tap Start Navigation for live turn-by-turn guidance along the cut.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature">
                    <div class="icon">
                        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><path d="M3 9h18M9 21V9"/></svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Show services</h3>
                    <p>Use the layers button to show locks, winding holes, water points and sanitary stations. Zoom in to see them.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature">
                    <div class="icon">
                        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M3 6l9-3 9 3v12l-9 3-9-3V6z"/></svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Set your boat</h3>
                    <p>Enter your boat's speed, length and beam so journey times and suitability are tailored to you.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="card">
                <details>
                    <summary>How are journey times calculated?</summary>
                    <p>Journey times combine the cruising distance at your chosen boat speed with time added for each lock and tunnel along the route. They're estimates to help you plan — real times vary with conditions, queues at locks, and how busy the network is.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Why are some waterways shown in red?</summary>
                    <p>Red sections are waterways that may not suit your boat's dimensions, based on the beam and length you've set. Narrow canals have a 7ft beam limit, so a wide-beam boat will see these in red. Always confirm specific restrictions before travelling.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>The map seems slow or canals don't appear straight away</summary>
                    <p>On the Cut loads canal detail for the area around you and fills in more as you move. If detail is missing, give it a moment or pan slightly. A good internet connection helps the first time you visit a new area, after which data is cached on your device.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>How accurate are the lock and service locations?</summary>
                    <p>Locks come from Canal &amp; River Trust open data. Water points, sanitary stations and winding holes come from OpenStreetMap, maintained by the boating community. Both are very good but not guaranteed complete or current — always carry up-to-date waterway guides.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Does the app work without signal?</summary>
                    <p>Canal data you've already loaded is cached on your device, so it remains available in areas with poor signal. The base map and any brand-new areas need a connection to load. It's wise to open your planned route while you still have signal.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Where do closures and stoppages come from?</summary>
                    <p>The notices feature links directly to the Canal &amp; River Trust's live notices page, so you always see their latest information. Always check this before setting off.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Does the app track or share my location?</summary>
                    <p>No. Your location is used only on your device to show your position and provide navigation. It is never collected, stored on a server, or shared with anyone. See the privacy policy for full details.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Which areas are covered?</summary>
                    <p>On the Cut covers the connected canal and navigable river network of England and Wales, including Canal &amp; River Trust waters, Environment Agency rivers, the Norfolk Broads, and smaller navigations.</p>
                </details>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Troubleshooting -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
            <div class="card">
                <details>
                    <summary>My route won't plan</summary>
                    <p>Make sure both your start and end points are on the connected network — tap close to a visible canal line so the app can snap to it. Very isolated or disconnected waterways may not route. If it persists, try points nearer the main network.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Navigation isn't following me</summary>
                    <p>Check that you've allowed location access for On the Cut in your device Settings → Privacy → Location Services. Navigation needs this to track your position.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>The app won't open after a week</summary>
                    <p>If you installed a test build directly, Apple's free signing expires after seven days and the app must be reinstalled. This does not happen with versions installed from the App Store.</p>
                </details>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Safety -->
        <div class="section">
            <div class="safety">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2L2 20h20L12 2z"/><path d="M12 9v5M12 17h.01"/></svg>
                <p><strong>Stay safe on the water.</strong> On the Cut is a planning and navigation aid only. Waterway data may be incomplete or out of date. Always check current Canal &amp; River Trust notices before travelling, carry up-to-date waterway guides, and use your own judgement on the water.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Contact -->
        <div class="section">
            <div class="contact">
                <h2>Still need help?</h2>
                <p>Happy to help with any question, problem or suggestion for the app.</p>
                <a class="btn" href="mailto:ayupduck@gmail.com?subject=On%20the%20Cut%20Support">Email Support</a>
                <p class="small">We aim to reply within a few days.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

    <footer>
        On the Cut is an independent app and is not affiliated with or endorsed by the Canal &amp; River Trust.<br>
        Map data © OpenStreetMap contributors. Waterway data from Canal &amp; River Trust Open Data.
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
